Here's a simple web game where holes appear on a human body image, and you need to click on them to score points. The holes will appear and disappear quickly. Below is the complete HTML code with embedded CSS and JavaScript:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Hole Clicker Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        #gameArea {
            position: relative;
            width: 300px;
            height: 600px;
            background-image: url('https://via.placeholder.com/300x600.png?text=Human+Body');
            background-size: cover;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .hole {
            position: absolute;
            width: 30px;
            height: 30px;
            background-color: red;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: none;
        }
        #score {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div id="score">Score: 0</div>
    <div id="gameArea"></div>

    <script>
        let score = 0;
        const scoreDisplay = document.getElementById('score');
        const gameArea = document.getElementById('gameArea');

        function createHole() {
            const hole = document.createElement('div');
            hole.classList.add('hole');
            hole.style.top = Math.random() * (gameArea.clientHeight - 30) + 'px';
            hole.style.left = Math.random() * (gameArea.clientWidth - 30) + 'px';
            gameArea.appendChild(hole);

            hole.style.display = 'block';

            hole.addEventListener('click', function() {
                score++;
                scoreDisplay.textContent = 'Score: ' + score;
                hole.remove();
            });

            setTimeout(() => {
                if (hole.parentNode) {
                    hole.remove();
                }
            }, 1000); // Hole disappears after 1 second
        }

        function startGame() {
            setInterval(createHole, 800); // New hole every 800ms
        }

        startGame();
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions to Use:
1. Copy the above code into a text editor.
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension, for example, `hole_clicker_game.html`.
3. Open the saved file in a web browser to play the game.

### Game Mechanics:
- A human body image is represented by a placeholder image.
- Red holes appear randomly on the body.
- Click on the holes to score points.
- Holes disappear after 1 second if not clicked. 
- A new hole appears every 800 milliseconds. 

Feel free to customize the image URL and styles as needed!
